3139	  \(\mathrm{eq\_of\_locally\_eq'}\) lives in the same file.}
3140	  For a sheaf \(F\) and a family of opens \(\{U_i\}\) with union \(V\), any family of sections
3141	  \(s_i \in F(U_i)\) agreeing on overlaps glues to a unique \(s \in F(V)\); and a section of \(V\)
3142	  is determined by its restrictions to a cover (\(\mathrm{eq\_of\_locally\_eq'}\)). These discharge
3143	  the existence and uniqueness obligations in the inductive step. The primed companion
3144	  \(\mathrm{existsUnique\_gluing'}\), which presents the same statement for a family of opens whose
3145	  supremum is a fixed open \(V\), is the form consumed by the cover-form descent
3146	  (\cref{lem:section_localization_descent_of_cover}).
3147	\end{lemma}
